Ninety percent of the crank generator MKII parts are printer.
The initial assembly was also completed.
But I made a mistake on a small part of the design and caused wrong distance setting.
Therefor, I'll have to remake some of the parts.

I've joined several 3D printing clubs on the Facebook for a couple of weeks.
Currently I feel the the atmosphere of discussion is nice.
But there were not many people who joined the discussion.
There are indeed some skilled 3D designers among the members.
I'll ry to get closer to the community by sharing my experiment results.



